modules.description: This module implements HTTP client operations for issuing requests over network connections using the Cohttp library. It supports standard HTTP methods like GET, POST, PUT, DELETE, and PATCH, with options to specify headers, request bodies, and chunked encoding. It works with URIs, Cohttp headers, and Lwt-based body streams, enabling asynchronous HTTP communication with concrete endpoints resolved via a context. Use cases include interacting with REST APIs, fetching web resources, and sending form data over HTTP or HTTPS.
